5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to crimes and offenses; to amend Section
10 13A-10-52, Code of Alabama 1975; to include various conditions
11 under which the crime of eluding or attempting to elude a law
12 enforcement officer is subject to heightened criminal
13 penalties; and to provide certain mandatory minimum penalties
14 for multiple convictions of eluding or attempting to elude a
15 law enforcement officer.
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
17 Section 1. Section 13A-10-52, Code of Alabama 1975, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 "§13A-10-52
20 (a) It shall be unlawful for a person to intentionally
21 flee by any means from anyone the person knows to be a law
22 enforcement officer if the person knows the officer is
23 attempting to arrest the person.
24 (b) It shall be unlawful for a person, while operating
25 a motor vehicle on a street, road, alley, or highway in this
26 state, to intentionally flee or attempt to elude a law
27 enforcement officer after having received a signal from the
28 officer to bring the vehicle to a stop.
Page 1

officer to bring the vehicle to a stop.
SB233 Engrossed
29 (c)(1) A violation of subsection (a) or (b) is a Class
30 A misdemeanorClass D felony.
31 (2) A violation of subsection (b) is a Class D felony.
32 (2)(3) A violation of subsection (a) or (b) is a Class
33 C felony if any of the following occur:
34 a. The flight or attempt to elude causes the offender
35 to strike or collide with another vehicle or pedestrian.
36 b. The flight or attempt to elude causes physical
37 injury to any other person.
38 c. The flight or attempt to elude results in the
39 offender crossing the lines of this state into a neighboring
40 state.
41 d. During the flight or attempt to elude, a child under
42 14 years of age is present in the vehicle.
43 e. The flight or attempt to elude occurs while the
44 offender is released on bail, probation, or parole, or while
45 the offender is serving a sentence in a community corrections
46 or work release program.
47 f. At the time of the offense, the offender has a
48 previous conviction for a violation of subsection (a) or (b).
49 (3)(4) A violation of subsection (a) or (b) is a Class
50 B felony if either any of the following occur:
51 a. The flight or attempt to elude causes serious
52 physical injury or death to any other person.
53 b. During the flight or attempt to elude, the person
54 exceeds 20 miles per hour over the legal maximum speed limit.
55 c. During the flight or attempt to elude, the offender
56 strikes or attempts to strike a law enforcement officer or a
Page 2

strikes or attempts to strike a law enforcement officer or a
SB233 Engrossed
57 vehicle occupied by a law enforcement officer.
58 d. At the time of the offense, the offender has two or
59 more previous convictions for a violation of subsection (a) or
60 (b).
61 (d)(1) Upon conviction for a violation of subsection
62 (a) or (b), the court shall order the suspension of the driver
63 license of the defendant for a period of not less than six
64 months nor more than two years.
65 (2) Upon a second conviction for a violation of
66 subsection (a) or (b) within a five year period of time, as
67 measured from the dates of previous arrests for which
68 convictions were obtained to the date of the current arrest
69 for which a conviction is obtained, the court shall sentence
70 the defendant to a minimum of 90 days confinement.
71 (3) Upon a third or subsequent conviction for a
72 violation of subsection (a) or (b) within a seven-year period
73 of time, as measured from the dates of previous arrests for
74 which convictions were obtained to the date of the current
75 arrest for which a conviction is obtained, the court shall
76 sentence the defendant to a minimum of 180 days confinement.
77 (e) It is not a violation of this section for an
78 individual to continue traveling at or below the speed limit,
79 with or without the vehicle's flashers turned on, with the
80 intent of stopping the vehicle at the nearest safe place."
81 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
82 1, 2026.
